<HEADLINE>
<P>
STUDY OF SEX LIVES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Re the survey on American's sexual practices (Oct. 7): Am I the only one who 
realizes that its impossible for men to have more sex partners (on average) 
than women do? I mean, if women only have two sex partners, and men have six, 
where do the extra four wome come from? Somebody's not telling the whole truth 
here. ROBERT WITTMOND Lakewood 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA102794-0012 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 092415 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
