<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCHOOLS: TEACHERS HELPING STUDENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I was delighted to read your extensive coverage of Broadway Elementary School 
("Frowns Turned Upside Down," Oct. 6). In the midst of a neighborhood plagued 
by sporadic gang violence, the principal, teachers and other school staff are 
offering an island of hope for their wonderful students. 
</P>
<P>
 Too often people will give up on a school because of the conditions around it. 
Your article showed how a school can focus positive energies from throughout 
our community and make a real difference for children. I hope your coverage 
will motivate more people and organizations to come forward and offer their 
assistance to Broadway and other schools throughout the Westside. There is no 
better investment of our time and energy. 
</P>
<P>
 MARK SLAVKIN 
</P>
<P>
 President, Board of Education Los Angeles Unified School District  
</P>
