<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL DAILY REPORT; ACROSS THE NATION; MIAMI RESERVE SUSPENDED 
INDEFINITELY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tremain Mack, a reserve defensive back for Miami, has been suspended 
indefinitely from the team after an altercation with police that led to his 
arrest. 
</P>
<P>
 Mack was charged with battery on a police officer, resisting arrest with 
violence and driving under the influence. He will not play Saturday against 
Virginia Tech and is not practicing with the team this week, Coach Dennis 
Erickson said. 
</P>
<P>
 According to Metro-Dade police, the altercation occurred early Sunday after an 
officer observed Mack driving erratically with a flat tire. Mack is scheduled 
to be arraigned Nov. 14. 
</P>
