<HEADLINE>
<P>
OCEAN CAT COMES BACK FOR TIE WITH DEMIN YENEM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ocean Cat rallied in the stretch to catch Demin Yenem and produce a dead heat 
in Wednesday's $50,500 Turbo Launch Stakes at Santa Anita's Oak Tree meeting. 
</P>
<P>
 Ocean Cat, ridden by Gary Stevens and carrying 115 pounds, paid $4, $2.40 and 
$2.60, and Denim Yenem, ridden by Corey Black and carrying 116 pounds, returned 
$2.40, $2.40 and $2.60. 
</P>
<P>
 The winners covered 6 1/2 furlongs in 1:16 2-5. 
</P>
