<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: HOLMES TO FIGHT MCCALL FOR TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Larry Holmes, who turns 45 in a week, will challenge WBC heavyweight champion 
Oliver McCall on Jan. 21. 
</P>
<P>
 George Foreman, who will be 46 on Jan. 10, will challenge Michael Moorer for 
the IBF and WBA heavyweight titles Nov. 5 at Las Vegas in what will be his 
first fight in 17 months. 
</P>
<P>
 It will be the 29-year-old McCall's first defense of the title he won on a 
shocking second-round knockout of Lennox Lewis on Sept. 25 at London. 
</P>
<P>
 Possible sites are Las Vegas or Atlantic City, N.J. 
</P>
<P>
 It will be Holmes' third bid at regaining at least a piece of the 
championship. 
</P>
<P>
 He failed to regain the IBF title from Michael Spinks when he lost a split 
decision in 1986, then retired. 
</P>
<P>
 Holmes came back to challenge Mike Tyson in 1988, was stopped in the fourth 
round and retired again. 
</P>
<P>
 From the time Holmes became champion by outpointing Ken Norton in 1978 until 
he lost it on points to Spinks in 1985, Holmes made 17 defenses of the WBC 
title, which he relinquished, and two defenses of the IBF title. 
</P>
</TEXT>
