<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: WHITTIER; SCHOOL BOARD TO NAME NEW MEMBER TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN CANALIS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Whittier City School District officials are expected to fill a vacant seat on 
the board today. 
</P>
<P>
 The original list of seven applicants has been narrowed to three: Nelda Foder, 
a Whittier College clerk-typist, Francisco Hidalgo, a professor at Cal State 
San Bernardino, and Theodore Saulino, a special-education teacher in Garvey 
School District. 
</P>
<P>
 The post was left vacant by Rosaura A. Aguerrebere. She had served on the 
board since December and resigned Sept. 7 after her husband, Joseph, accepted a 
job with the Ford Foundation in New York City. 
</P>
<P>
 The new board member will serve until November, 1995, when the district will 
hold another election to decide who will serve the remaining two years of 
Aguerrebere's term. JOHN CANALIS 
</P>
</TEXT>
