<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: COMMERCE; VOLUNTEERS SOUGHT FOR DISASTER TRAINING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city is seeking volunteers who will be trained to help authorities assess 
damage and provide aid during disasters. 
</P>
<P>
 The city will provide the training free of charge. Volunteers should be 
physically fit and available to work at times requested by the city. 
</P>
<P>
 Duties may include helping direct out-of-town emergency workers around the 
city, taking stock of damage or assisting officials at shelters run by the city 
and American Red Cross. 
</P>
<P>
 All volunteers will receive training in first aid and cardiopulmonary 
resuscitation. Training sessions will be at the City Hall Annex, 5550 Harbor 
St., today from 6:30 to 9:30 p.m. and Saturday from 9 a.m. to 4 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 887-4460, Ext. 2809. 
</P>
</TEXT>
