<P>
COLLAPSED BRIDGE'S MAKER TO DONATE A NEW ONE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The builder of a bridge that collapsed here Friday, killing 32 people, said 
Wednesday that it will build a new bridge and donate it to the government. 
</P>
<P>
 Dong Ah Construction Co. said it plans to spend $186 million and use a 
Japanese design to build the new bridge across Seoul's Han River to replace the 
collapsed one. 
</P>
<P>
 Dong Ah Chairman Choi Won Suk said his company will also donate $12 million to 
improve the safety of Seoul's bridges. 
</P>
