<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; ACLU SPONSORS ESSAY CONTEST ON PROP. 187 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALICIA DI RADO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 High school students interested in immigration and current affairs in 
California are invited to participate in an essay contest about Proposition 
187. 
</P>
<P>
 The Orange County chapter of the American Civil Liberties Union is sponsoring 
a contest called "Immigrants, California and Proposition 187: An Essay." 
</P>
<P>
 Proposition 187, which will appear on the November ballot, is the so-called 
"Save Our State" initiative, which would restrict government benefits to 
undocumented immigrants. Contest judges will be looking for entries that 
thoughtfully analyze the impact of Proposition 187 on the state, said Sam 
Mistrano, ACLU legislative director in Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 Essays should be two to four pages long. The winner will be awarded $100, and 
the winning essay will be published in the ACLU's "Open Forum" newsletter. 
</P>
<P>
 Entries should be submitted to: ACLU Immigrant Issues Essay Contest, 14252 
Culver, Suite A -- 570, Irvine CA 92714-1918. All entries must be postmarked by 
Nov. 20. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 977-9500, Ext. 261.ALICIA DI RADO 
</P>
</TEXT>
