<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY ALMANAC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It's not Manhattan, but Orange County holds its own when it comes to corporate 
power. 
</P>
<P>
 According to Fortune magazine, the county is home to four of the top companies 
on the Fortune 500 list. 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine appears to be the local center of corporate wealth: The city is home to 
three of the county's four top companies. 
</P>
<P>
 Figures reflect 1993 financial activity, in millions: Fortune in Sales 
(Fortune 500 rank) Rockwell, Seal Beach (45): $10,840 AST Research, Irvine 
(287): $1,412 Western Digital, Irvine (318): $1, 225 Allergan, Irvine (384): 
$888 Today 
</P>
<P>
 A debate on Measure A, the El Toro Airport Initiative, begins at 7 p.m. at the 
Irvine City Council chambers. 
</P>
<P>
 The forum, sponsored by the Irvine Chamber of Commerce, will also be televised 
live on Dimension Cable Channel 3. 
</P>
<P>
 Supporters and opponents of a commercial airport at El Toro will participate 
in the forum. Irvine City Atty. Joel D. Kuperberg will describe the initiative 
and its potential impact on the city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
