<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: PLACENTIA; BRIDGE COMPETITION TO BENEFIT ARTS PROGRAMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HOLLY J. WAGNER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Placentia's Cultural Arts Commission will lay it out in spades at its fourth 
annual Evening of Bridge at the Backs on Nov. 4. 
</P>
<P>
 Admission of $10 per person includes a choice of playing party bridge or 
duplicate bridge for prizes, including dinner for two at Marie Callender's, a 
night at a Marriott hotel, a night at a Fairfield Inn hotel, and gift 
certificates to El Torito, Rembrandt's and the North Orange County Bridge Club. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets must be purchased by Friday. The tournament will be at 7:30 p.m. Nov. 
4 at Backs Community Building, 201 N. Bradford Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 Proceeds will benefit arts programs in the city. For more information or 
tickets, call (714) 993-8232.HOLLY J. WAGNER 
</P>
