<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: FOUNTAIN VALLEY; RIVER PROJECT DIRECTOR TO SPEAK AT 
BREAKFAST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DEBRA CANO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Terrie Medeiros, the county's director of the Santa Ana River Project, will be 
the guest speaker at today's Mayor's Breakfast. 
</P>
<P>
 Medeiros will talk about the status of the Santa Ana River Mainstem Project. 
This topic is timely in view of the difficulties residents have experienced in 
seeking a reduction in the cost of flood insurance, city officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Mayor John J. Collins will host the 8 a.m. breakfast in the Saltzer Conference 
Room of Fountain Valley Regional Hospital and Medical Center, 17100 Euclid St. 
at Warner Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 Reservations: (714) 965-4400. DEBRA CANO 
</P>
