<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: UNIVERSAL CITY; MAN DIES, 2 INJURED IN HEAD-ON CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TIMOTHY WILLIAMS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man was killed and two other people were injured when a car traveling the 
wrong way on the Hollywood Freeway collided head-on with another vehicle, the 
California Highway Patrol said. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident occurred about 8 p.m. Tuesday on the northbound side of the 
freeway after Shawna Leavell, 29, of Encino, entered the freeway via an 
off-ramp, said CHP Officer Tito Gomez. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities say they do not know how long she was driving the wrong way. 
</P>
<P>
 Near Universal City, Leavell's car struck a car traveling northbound, driven 
by Yuri Avetisyan, 46, of North Hollywood, Gomez said. 
</P>
<P>
 Avetisyan was pronounced dead at the scene, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 On Wednesday, Leavell and a passenger in Avetisyan's car were in serious 
condition at Holy Cross Medical Center in Mission Hills, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Leavell has been charged with driving under the influence of alcohol, Gomez 
said. TIMOTHY WILLIAMS 
</P>
</TEXT>
