<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: RANCHO SANTA MARGARITA; STAFF FILLING SHELVES AT NEW 
COUNTY LIBRARY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The county has begun stocking its new library.  
</P>
<P>
 A move-in crew and library staff this week started putting books on shelves, 
installing computers and arranging furniture in the facility at 30902 La 
Promesa Drive. 
</P>
<P>
 The library's grand opening is scheduled for Nov. 29. 
</P>
<P>
 The 16,300-square-foot facility will hold 81,300 volumes and include a 
storytelling terrace, computer access reference, study areas, a magazine lounge 
with fireplace, and a community room. 
</P>
<P>
 The library is a joint project between the county and the Santa Margarita Co. 
JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
