<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: BUENA PARK; POSSIBLE ANTI-GAY ATTACK IS PROBED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KEN ELLINGWOOD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Authorities are investigating a possible gay-bashing attack Sunday on two men 
near a Buena Park bar that has a gay clientele. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said a group of three to five men shouted anti-gay epithets in Spanish, 
slashed the victims with broken bottles and beat them before stealing the car 
in which the two were talking while parked near Ozz, a bar and restaurant on 
Manchester Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
 Police were seeking the attackers Wednesday. The victims' car -- stripped and 
badly damaged -- was found several blocks away on Monday, said Sgt. Robert F. 
Chaney. 
</P>
<P>
 Tomas Canas, 32, of Fullerton suffered a fractured skull in the attack and was 
released Wednesday night from St. Jude Medical Center in Fullerton. Alex 
Saucedo, 26, of Long Beach was treated at the same hospital for severe cuts and 
bruises to the face and head. 
</P>
<P>
 The two were sitting in Canas' car in a parking lot across the street from the 
bar when the men approached and pulled them from the car, Chaney said. Canas 
said in a brief interview from his hospital room that attackers yelled epithets 
and cursed as they beat him and Saucedo. KEN ELLINGWOOD 
</P>
