<HEADLINE>
<P>
STUFFED TURKEYS SEIZED IN GUN-SMUGGLING PLOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two Haitians living in South Florida have admitted a scheme to stuff 
semiautomatic pistols into turkeys and smuggle them into Haiti. 
</P>
<P>
 Patrick Louiseau and Florence Toussaint pleaded guilty Monday to federal 
firearms charges. 
</P>
<P>
 Louiseau and Toussaint thawed out frozen turkeys and stuffed two or three 
.380-caliber pistols into each. Then they froze the turkeys anew, packed them 
in their luggage and carried 20 guns to Haiti on May 17, authorities said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
