COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: HOSTS SOUGHT FOR EXCHANGE STUDENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KAY SAILLANT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Organizers of a cultural exchange program are looking for families willing to 
share their Thanksgiving holiday with a high school student from Japan. 
</P>
<P>
 Twenty-eight students from Nishitan High School in Fukuoka, Japan, will arrive 
in Ventura County on Nov. 19, said Roxanne Kelley, a coordinator for Cultural 
Homestay International. 
</P>
<P>
 Many of the students have already been matched with families, but four boys 
and two girls still need to be placed, Kelley said. 
</P>
<P>
 The students will stay with the host family through the Thanksgiving holiday, 
departing for Japan on Nov. 28, she said. 
</P>
<P>
 All of the students are 16 or 17 years old, she said. 
</P>
<P>
 "Thanksgiving is a uniquely American holiday," Kelley said. "The purpose of 
the trip is for them to learn about Thanksgiving and its place in American 
culture." 
</P>
<P>
 Besides sharing Thanksgiving with families, the students will visit Ventura 
County high schools, Kelley said. All the Japanese students are fully insured 
and bring their own spending money, she said. KAY SAILLANT 
</P>
