COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: OXNARD COLLEGE PLANS WOMEN'S CELEBRATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Oxnard College will hold a Women's Day Celebration on Saturday that will 
include workshops, seminars, speakers and a fashion show, all geared toward 
women. 
</P>
<P>
 The one-day program will feature speakers such as Sheila Cluff, the creator 
and owner of two spas -- The Oaks at Ojai and The Palms at Palm Springs -- and 
physician Ruby Simpkins speaking on chronic fatigue syndrome. 
</P>
<P>
 The celebration also will include 24 workshops with topics ranging from 
parenting practices and self-esteem to makeup and finances. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's a day for women to celebrate who they are, to discover that we are not 
alone," said Amy Stroba, one of the program's organizers. "We hope to inspire 
women to rediscover their dreams and go on to make them happen." 
</P>
<P>
 The eighth annual celebration of women will begin at 8 a.m. and end at 2:45 
p.m. The program will cost $25, which includes a continental breakfast and 
lunch. 
</P>
<P>
 The fee for senior citizens and full-time students will be $20. For more 
information, call 986-5833. CHRISTINA LIMA 
