<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; AUSTRIA; FORMER SYRIAN ENVOY IS ARRESTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Syria's former ambassador to East Germany has been arrested on suspicion of 
helping to provide explosives to terrorist Carlos the Jackal, police said.The 
former diplomat was identified by the Austrian Press Agency as Faisal Summak. 
He was arrested in a Vienna hotel on an international warrant. Police said the 
Syrian ambassador from 1981 to 1989 ordered an aide to supply 15 pounds of 
explosives to Carlos, who was captured in August and now awaits trial in Paris. 
</P>
