<HEADLINE>
<P>
EX-YUGOSLAV FEDERATION GETS NEW U.S. ENVOY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Charles H. Thomas, a career foreign service officer, has been appointed 
special U.S. envoy to the former Yugoslav federation, the State Department said 
Wednesday. He succeeds Charles Redman, who has become ambassador to Germany. 
</P>
<P>
 Thomas, a former ambassador to Hungary, most recently was executive director 
of the State Department's Senior Policy Group for Central and Eastern Europe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
