<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY; CANCER: LOW-COST SCREENINGS OFFERED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An East Valley health center is offering reduced-cost breast and cervical 
cancer screenings through November, aimed at low-income women who otherwise 
might not receive basic health services. 
</P>
<P>
 At East Valley Community Health Center clinics in West Covina and Pomona, the 
screening charge will range from $5 to $30, based on annual income. The 
screening includes a pelvic exam, Pap smear, breast exam and educational 
materials. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: West Covina, (818) 919-5724; Pomona, (909) 620-8088. 
</P>
</TEXT>
