<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: WEST VALLEY; MTA DONATES RAILROAD ARTIFACTS TO MUSEUMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Metropolitan Transportation Authority is donating railroad artifacts 
dating back to the early 1900s to museums and other organizations dedicated to 
preserving history. 
</P>
<P>
 The artifacts, including old rails, crossing gates and a cantilever signal 
bridge, are being removed to make way for construction of the Pasadena Blue 
Line. 
</P>
</TEXT>
