<TEXT>
<P>
 California Energy Wins Magma Shareholder List: A Nevada state court ruled that 
Magma Power Co. must supply the Omaha-based company with the names.California 
Energy Co. is attempting a hostile takeover. Last Friday, the geothermal power 
company boosted its bid for San Diego-based Magma Power to $38.50 a share, or 
$925 million, from its earlier offer of $35 a share, or $840 million. The court 
ruled late Monday that Magma must provide the shareholders' names to Ben Holt, 
a director of California Energy who is also a Magma shareholder. Holt had sued 
Magma individually to obtain the list. "It's not a significant setback," said 
Jon Peele, Magma's general counsel. 
