<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL NOTES: CLAY MCKNIGHT DECIDES TO GO TO UC IRVINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Clay McKnight of Mater Dei orally committed to play basketball at UC Irvine, 
Monarch Athletic Director Gary McKnight said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 "We've been fortunate to see a lot of kids come through our school and earn 
scholarships," said Gary McKnight, also Mater Dei's basketball coach."But it's 
kind of neat to see it happen for your own son. It's an exciting time for our 
family. 
</P>
<P>
 "(Irvine Coach) Rod Baker did a great job working with us and Clay will get a 
real chance to play right away." 
</P>
<P>
 McKnight, a 6-foot-2 guard, averaged 14.6 points and shot 54% from the field 
for Mater Dei last season. The Monarchs finished 33-1 and won the Southern 
Section Division I-A championship before losing to Los Angeles Crenshaw in the 
Southern California Regional Division I final. 
</P>
<P>
 McKnight, a second-team Times All-County selection, was the South Coast League 
most valuable player and made 49% (95 of 192) of his three-pointers and 86% of 
his free throws last season. MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
