<HEADLINE>
<P>
A LITTLE BIT OF HISTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Canoga Park High won the City Section football championship in 1968 with a 
34-27 victory over Poly before 14,000 at East Los Angeles College. 
</P>
<P>
 Running back Bob Adams scored all five touchdowns for Coach Jack Mathieson's 
"Green Machine."  
</P>
<P>
 Canoga Park, which finished 10-1-1, also defeated Westchester, 27-6; Gardena, 
7-6; and Manual Arts, 14-13, in the playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
 Adams, who rushed for 1,545 yards, was named City player of the year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA102794-0407 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 092811 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
