<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: BOXING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sugar Shane Mosley has been pulled out of the co-main boxing event scheduled 
for Nov. 2 at the Warner Center Marriott. 
</P>
<P>
 Fight organizers and Mosley's managers could not agree on an opponent, 
promoter Peter Broudy said Wednesday.Mosley, a lightweight from Pomona, is 15-0 
with 14 knockouts. 
</P>
<P>
 Martin Krastev, a superbantamweight from Simi Valley, also has been scratched 
from the card. He has pneumonia. 
</P>
<P>
 Broudy said he expects to have replacements to complete the six-bout show by 
the end of the week. In the main event, P.J. Goossen of Palmdale (12-0, 11 
knockouts) will meet Irish Pat Lawlor of San Francisco (20-5, six knockouts) in 
a 10-round superwelterweight bout. Basketball 
</P>
<P>
 Cal State Northridge's basketball opener against UCLA on Nov. 26 at Pauley 
Pavilion will be televised live on Prime Ticket starting at 2 p.m. Football 
</P>
<P>
 Canyon High will activate receiver Zamien Calvin for Friday night's game 
against Saugus. Calvin transferred from Quartz Hill after moving to Canyon 
earlier this month. 
</P>
<P>
 The 6-foot-2, 180-pound senior had not caught a pass for the Rebels, but Coach 
Larry Mohr said he will play for the Cowboys. 
</P>
<P>
 "He's got some speed, he's athletic," Mohr said. "I think he'll help this 
team." Baseball 
</P>
<P>
 Several major and minor league players are scheduled for an exhibition against 
local college players at Blair Field in Long Beach on Oct. 29 and Oct. 30. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: 818-225-7571. 
</P>
</TEXT>
