<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; CLU'S STREAK IN SOCCER ENDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Occidental's Jocelyn Ferialdi scored her second goal with 15 minutes remaining 
to give the Tigers a 3-2 victory over Cal Lutheran in a Southern California 
Intercollegiate Athletic Assn. women's soccer match Wednesday at Thousand Oaks. 
</P>
<P>
 The loss is Cal Lutheran's first in conference play in four seasons and 47 
matches. The Regals had four shots in the final five minutes. Carla Crawford 
scored both goals for Cal Lutheran (13-5, 10-1 in conference play). 
</P>
<P>
 Michelle Winscott scored in the 14th minute to give Occidental (13-2-1, 8-2-1) 
a 1-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 GIRLS' TENNIS 
</P>
<P>
 Agoura 15, Cate 3 -- No. 1 singles player Sherry Reese swept three sets, 
including a 6-3 victory over Cate's ranked junior, Erica Altman. Junior Audry 
Boesflug, playing her first varsity match, won two of three sets at No. 3 
singles in a nonleague match against the seventh-ranked team in Division IV. 
</P>
<P>
 At No. 1 doubles, Galit Hadari and Sabrina Lundquist (44-4 this season) swept 
for Agoura (13-4). 
</P>
<P>
 WATER POLO 
</P>
<P>
 Calabasas 28, Villanova Prep 4 -- The Coyotes eclipsed their best offensive 
output of the season by nine goals in a Frontier League game at Calabasas.  
</P>
<P>
 Senior Terry Marciano had nine goals to lead Calabasas (5-10, 3-4). David 
Garrett added four goals and Alex Hettena, Steve Hever and Matt Shapira scored 
three goals each for the Coyotes. 
</P>
<P>
 Loyola 15, Crespi 11 -- The Celts were outscored, 7-1, in the third quarter 
after Mike Scarcelli, Crespi's leading scored was ejected in a Mission League 
match at Loyola.  
</P>
<P>
 Scarcelli and David Brea had three goals each for Crespi (13-10, 4-3). Brendan 
Beer, Peter Baldwin and Ethan Holmes each had four goals for Loyola. 
</P>
<P>
 Harvard-Westlake 21, Notre Dame 12 -- Albert Won scored seven goals as the 
Wolverines had a six-goal advantage by halftime of a Mission League game. 
</P>
<P>
 Doug Kazarian and David Stone had two goals each for Harvard (14-3, 7-0). Theo 
Smit led Notre Dame with four goals. 
</P>
<P>
 GIRLS' VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Nordhoff d. Santa Ynez, 13-15, 15-6, 15-5, 15-11 -- Jami Sawyer had 25 kills 
and Jodi Ferro 20 to help the Rangers (10-1) upset Santa Ynez in a nonleague 
match. Santa Ynez (9-2) was ranked second in Division IV, Nordhoff third. Julie 
Sandefur had 28 assists. 
</P>
<P>
 Poly d. North Hollywood, 15-13, 15-7, 15-9 -- Donna Farraj had 10 kills for 
the Parrots (7-4, 5-4) in a Valley Pac-8 Conference match. Samantha Fargeon had 
11 kills and three aces for North Hollywood (5-7, 3-6). 
</P>
<P>
 Van Nuys d. Reseda 15-6, 15-4, 15-4 -- Connie Cho had eight kills and Connie 
Chae added five kills and 15 assists for the Wolves (12-0, 10-0) in a Valley 
Pac-8 Conference match. 
</P>
</TEXT>
