<P>
NEWS BITES : FRONTIER WINE HATS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BARBARA HANSEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Want to cap your Cabernet in style? Buy an authentic coonskin topper from Davy 
Crockett himself.The furry bottle closers, handmade of genuine raccoon fur, are 
on sale at the Fess Parker Winery and Vineyard for $10. (There are coonskin 
caps suitable for human wear, too, but they're made from rabbit fur: $13.) 
Actor/winery-owner Parker, who immortalized the famous frontiersman on 
television and in the movies, debuted in the role on Dec. 12, 1954. Most 
weekends, he's out of the saddle and in the winery signing bottles. The winery 
is at 6200 Foxen Canyon Road, Los Olivos, Calif. 93441; or call (800) 841-1104. 
BARBARA HANSEN 
</P>
